The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 19 December is 129,937 (14,976 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 14 December, there were 5,810 new confirmed cases (669.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 07 December, there were 5,602 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 4% (208 extra cases).
